<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-27"><hi rend="italic">April 27,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your dispatch of the 11th
                        instant, concerning the enforcement of the Bering Sea regulations and
                        calling attention to the use of the word “exclusive” in section 1 of the act
                        approved April 6, 1894.</p>
                    <p>For your information, I inclose copy of the Department’s note of the 18th
                            instant<note n="1" xml:id="d196fn1">See <ref target="#pg_177">p.
                                177</ref>.</note> on this subject to the British ambassador at the
                        capital, together with six copies of an act of Congress, approved April 24,
                        1894, wherein the error referred to is corrected.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>